 per cast.<br><br>1.9 seconds per casts means roughly 6 seconds of melee time for 3 casts.  Even at 100 dps thats 600 dmg. Less than epic skin.<br><br>What about duelist? 1 round 200 on a crappy round 800 on a good one. (1300 on a great one but that should be about when he hits his yonder key)<br><br>So maybe on a flawless execution with good rolls I'll drop his epic skin and knock 40-50% of his hp off.<br><br>Thats assuming he doesn't get any free nukes in through hit and run tactics or lev or ghosting or well and so on.<br><br>Underpowered indeed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uauroreakengro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aurore Akengro</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/13/02 5:35:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Those damn underpowered wizzies. *warning short log file</span><hr size=1> Some info for you:<br><br>Lure of ice does 519 in PvP. No more, no less. As your log shows, you are hit for 561 and 534. This is over the 'magic' 519, hence Voltaic was using a dmg enhancement item.<br><br>Moreover, the cast time of Lure of Ice is 4.5 seconds. Your log only shows 1 time where Voltaic is casting it, and it fires off, the time difference does not prove much, since it could be anything between 4 and 5 seconds, but you have to agree that if he has a damage bracer, he prolly has a shortening time thing item ;p<br><br>Also for your information, Voltaic has AA spell crits.<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 1.9 seconds per casts means roughly 6 seconds of melee time for 3 casts. Even at 100 dps thats 600 dmg. Less than epic skin.<br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>But by that time your BS will have recycled, so every hit, you get in a free BS attempt. Which means you can easily top at 200-300 dps in those conditions. <br><br><br>Why the heck are you whining? Because if he gets in trouble he gates and 'heals' up? Why do you have to want to win all the encounters? Do you realise not all wizards have an epic? Do you realise that if skin goes down mid fight you are practically garanteed an interrupt. Then all he will be trying to do is get out of range to yonder, use ranged weapons maybe?<br><br><br>Also, I'm pretty surprised that Latnim wasn't nuking you as well. <br><br>But obviously your real beef is with wiz epic. Do you know that yonder doesn't always take you far enough to get a clean 12+ seconds to rebuff? Do you realise in the meantime you can walk away? <p>Aurore<HR>~Seekers of Divinity~<BR>Sorceress of <a href=http://www.ralloszek.net>Rallos Zek</a><BR><a href=http://www.progressquest.com><img src=http://www-rocq.inria.fr/~bnguyen/pony.gif></img></a>The Pony with the Pointy Hat.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/14/02 3:53:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Those damn underpowered wizzies. *warning short log file</span><hr size=1> Your right he was using focus items. Sorry my mistake.  He still could have stuck with lures and killed me before I broke epic skin and i was backstabbing. Once right at the start of the fight.  Then another 11 seconds later.  