r it as far as pvp gains regardless of skill unless they chooses to gang bang pk with some casters. Is the grass really greener?<br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Nope but if you just run around always in no drop gear then you won't lose anything, if that's your problem. The point is, if a wiz ran around with gear, he'd have lost it all pretty fast. That's why they run around with nothing, and get stuff when they kill people. Is it fair? No, but up to you to chose the way you want to PvP, be it by risking gear and having a slight advantage to using it, or by going no risk, and possibly losing some effectiveness.<br><br>Are wiz the perfect PK-Ebay class? Yes I agree. Do wizards fit my view of balanced PvP, in so far as they have a chance against every class, no not at all. The PK-Ebay wizards are simply using the best tool for their ends (ie get loot off players regardless of the number of times they die themselves.<br><br>This is quite a different discussion from the fact that wizards are good in PvP or not. I don't call dying 10 times and killing 1 monk and looting a fungus tunic a class balanced in PvP. I have my views on PvP; and Sullon is imo the best PvP server from the ruleset, because even if they are scoring points, those wiz are taking the deaths (albeit small with xp res but still) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ullyapakadeabn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llyap aka Deabn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/21/02 9:11:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pffffff</span><hr size=1> Aerimus wrote: &quot;Wizards have always been the favored pk class on RZ.&quot;<br><br>Wizards are a favored 